            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>orange<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> </strong>in half</p><p>Combine the<strong> </strong>juice<strong> </strong>of the<strong> orange<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> rice vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp<strong> </strong><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[80ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>ground paprika</strong> and <strong>cornflour</strong> to the bowl and whisk everything together – this is your<strong> Filipino-style tocino sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
